                    "updated": "2006-11-03T08:00:28.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/11129",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Resolved in revision 1446 in SVN",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2006-11-03T11:09:54.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2006-11-03T11:09:54.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/11138",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=lars",
                        "name": "lars",
                        "displayName": "Lars Strojny",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "The fix here is incorrect. It will  continue to double escape the strings. The thing is, if a Zend_XmlRpc_Value_String object is created, it just encodes the submitted string to make it XML-safe. But: DomElement also encodes the string so getValue() should be used and not $this->_value.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=lars",
                        "name": "lars",
                        "displayName": "Lars Strojny",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2006-11-03T20:55:41.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2006-11-03T20:55:41.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/11157",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Took me a bit to figure out where the getValue() should be done, but found it -- it's in Zend_XmlRpc_Value_Scalar, and the change is committed in 1474. Please test.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2006-11-05T22:06:49.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2006-11-05T22:06:49.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/11159",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=lars",
                        "name": "lars",
                        "displayName": "Lars Strojny",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Sorry, I would have explained that better. But it works now.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=lars",
                        "name": "lars",
                        "displayName": "Lars Strojny",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2006-11-06T05:47:41.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2006-11-06T05:47:41.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/11160",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=lars",
                        "name": "lars",
                        "displayName": "Lars Strojny",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I do not want to fell on your nerves but I found another related thing. The Zend_XmlRpc_Value_Base64 has a similiar problem. As we are using $this->getValue() now it will return an unencoded binary which is incorrect. As I'm currently using Base64-stuff just for sending, not for receiving I hotfixed that by returning the base64-encoded string, which is incorrect if you receive a string from the server because it will still be base64-encoded. So I guess we ran into a design problem. String values will be encoded twice, as long as we do not $this->getValue() but base64-values will not be encoded, if we use $this->getValue(). I'm not sure currently how to fix this.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=lars",
                        "name": "lars",
                        "displayName": "Lars Strojny",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2006-11-06T10:27:10.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2006-11-06T10:27:10.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
    },
